text: Zielone () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Lewin Kłodzki, within Kłodzko County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately east of Lewin Kłodzki, west of Kłodzko, and south-west of the regional capital Wrocław. ==References== Zielone
